            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Sumerians</h3>In the map in this section, we highlight the region where Sumerian cities flourished.</p>",
               "source": [],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "The Sumerians did not form a unified country. The various cities that arose across a large territory—from Mesopotamia to the Zagros Mountains in present-day Iran—were organized as independent city-states. These Sumerian city-states were eventually dominated by the Elamites, bringing an end to a period that lasted from approximately <htdate0> to <htdate1>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "5be12554-c54b-4a38-b24c-5a0842fdfd9d",
                     "text": "Kessler, P. L.",
                     "page": "Map of Sumer",
                     "date_time": {
